<DocLayout
    title="Getting Started - gsheetbase"
    description="Get started with gsheetbase in 5 minutes"
>
    <article class="prose prose-slate dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
        <h1>Getting Started with gsheetbase</h1>

        <p>
            Welcome! This guide will help you set up gsheetbase and create your
            first database-powered spreadsheet in just a few minutes.
        </p>

        <h2>1. Installation</h2>
        <p>First, install the gsheetbase package:</p>
        <pre><code class="language-bash">npm install gsheetbase</code></pre>

        <h2>2. API Key Setup</h2>
        <p>
            Create a free account at <a href="https://gsheetbase.com"
                >gsheetbase.com</a
            > and get your API key from the dashboard.
        </p>

        <h2>3. First Query</h2>
        <p>Here's a simple example to fetch data from your spreadsheet:</p>
        <pre><code class="language-javascript">{`const gsheetbase = require('gsheetbase');

const db = new gsheetbase({
  apiKey: 'your-api-key-here',
  spreadsheetId: 'your-spreadsheet-id'
});

// Fetch all data
const data = await db.query().select('*').get();
console.log(data);`}</code></pre>

